  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of this study is to investigate the incidence of falling in a cohort of
      patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) referred to a pulmonary
      rehabilitation program and to verify the risk factors. The secondary aim is to verify whether
      available balance assessment tools are feasible in clinical practice and which tools and
      values can best predict falls in people with COPD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
